Description: Sold by players. For players. 2013 PRS SE Santana Quilted Maple Top Electric Guitar - Vintage Sunburst See our other items Carlos Santana’s influence as a PRS artist led to the development of our SE electric guitar series, which launched in 2001. In honor of that legacy, PRS is proud to offer the SE Santana model. The SE Santana features a 24.5” scale length on a 24 fret neck, the PRS patented molded tremolo, Santana "S" humbuckers, and the same Santana body shape silhouette as Santana’s revered American-made PRS models. This particular guitar has black fleck in the finish on the top near the pickup selector and some minor wear on the pickup covers. There is a scuff in the clearcoat on the face of the headstock and a small nick in the clearcoat on the side of the body, not far from the rear strap button. These signs of use are very subtle and we have included close up photos at just the right angles to make sure you can see them. How Does It Play? We have given this guitar a nice professional setup to make sure it is 100% ready to play. It has a straight neck and nice action, free of fretbuzz. WE DO HAVE THE TREMOLO ARM! We're sorry we forgot to include it in the photos. But we actually bought a brand new PRS brand trem arm for it, correct to this model, and it is included. A new Guardian Cases hardshell case can be added to US orders for $75 or to international orders for $95.
